{
  "texts": [
    "Planning with an External Move ValidatorIn our final experiment with the external move validator, no model solved a single puzzle.",
    "As shown in Fig. 6, this intervention hurt performance, lowering the success rates of all models and shifting the dominant failure mode to looping in most models and early termination in GPT-5-mini.",
    "Fig. 7 further illustrates the planning deficit, showing that the models made minimal progress toward the goal state despite making numerous valid moves.",
    "For instance, GPT-5-mini made, on average, nearly forty-seven valid moves to achieve only about six moves of progress based on a Manhattan-distance heuristic.",
    "GPT-5-Thinking and Gemini were more efficient in that they made better progress in fewer moves, but this matters little, as they often began to repeat moves, completely stagnating progress."
  ]
}